obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line 3
  line `THE AGRICULTU RAL AND PROCESSED FOOD PRODUCTS EXPORT DEVELOPMENT`
  line `AUTHORITY ACT, 1985`
  line `A CT N O. 2 OF 1 986`
  line `[ 8th January, 1986. ]`
  line `An Act to provide for the establishment of an Authority for the development and promotion o f`
  line `exports of certain agricultural and processed food products and for matters connected`
  line therewith.
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Thirty - sixth Year of th e Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `1. Short title, extent and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the Agricultural and`
  line `Processed Food Products Export Development Authority Act, 1985.`
  line `( 2 ) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line `( 3 ) It shall come into force on such date 1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “ Authority ” means the Agricultural and Processed Food Products Export Developme nt`
  line `Authority established under s ection 4;`
  line `( b ) “ Chairman ” means the Chairman of the Authority;`
  line `( c ) “ export ” means taking out of India by land, sea or air;`
  line `( d ) “ exporter ” means a person registered as an exporter of Scheduled products under s ection 12;`
  line `( e ) “ member ” means a member of the Authority an d includes the Chairman;`
  line `( f ) “ prescribed ” means prescrib ed by rules made under this Act;`
  line `( g ) “ processing ” in relation to 2 [Scheduled products o r, as the case may be, Special p roducts]`
  line `includes the process of preservation of such products such as canning, free zing, drying, salting,`
  line `smoking, peeling or filleting and any other method of proc essing which the Authority may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf;`
  line `( h ) “ regulations ” means regulations made under this Act;`
  line `( i ) “ Scheduled pr oduct ” means any of the agricultural or proc essed food products included in`
  line `3 [the First Schedule];`
  line `4 [( j ) “ Special product ” means any of the agricultural or processed food products included in the`
  line `Second Schedule.]`
  line `5 [ 3. Power to amend the Schedule. — The Central Government may, having regard to the objects to`
  line `this Act, and if it considers necessary or expedient so to do, by notification in the Official Gazette, add to,`
  line `or, as the case may be, omit from, the First Schedule or the Second Schedule any agricul tural or processed`
  line `food product and on such addition, or as the case may be, omission, such product shall be, or shall cease`
  line `to be, a Scheduled product or Special product as the case may be.]`
  line `1. 13 th February, 1986, vide n otification No. S. O. 55( E ), dated 13 th February, 1986, s ee Gazette of India, 1986, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, s ec. 3( ii ).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 2009, s. 2, for “Scheduled products” (w.e.f. 13 - 10 - 2008 ).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “the Schedule ” (w.e.f. 13 - 10 - 2008 ).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 13 - 10 - 2008 ).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 3. ibid., for section 3 (w.e.f. 13 - 10 - 2008 ).`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
