obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `A GRICULTURAL AND P ROCESSED F OOD P RODUCTS E XPORT D EVELOPMENT A UTHORITY`
  line `4. Establishment and constitution of the Authority. — ( 1 ) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf, there shall be established`
  line `for the purposes of this Act, an Authority to be called the Agricultural and Processed Food Products`
  line `Export Development Authority.`
  line `( 2 ) The Authority shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal, with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property, both movable and immovable, and to`
  line `contract, and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line `( 3 ) The head office of the Authority shall be at Delhi and the Authority may, with the previous`
  line `approval of the Central Government, establish offices or agencies at other places in or outside India.`
  line `( 4 ) The A uthority shall consist of the following members, namely: —`
  line `( a ) a Chairman, to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line `( b ) the Agricultural Marketing Adviser to the Government of India, ex officio;`
  line `( c ) one member to be appointed by the Central Government to re present the Planning`
  line Commission;
  line `( d ) three members of Parliament of whom two shall be elected by the House of the People a nd`
  line `one by the Council of States;`
  line `( e ) eight members to be appointed by the Central Government to represent, respectively, the`
  line `Ministries of the Central Government dealing with —`
  line `( i ) ag riculture and rural deve lopment;`
  line `( ii ) commerce;`
  line `( iii ) f inance;`
  line `( iv ) industry;`
  line `( v ) food;`
  line `( vi ) civil supplies;`
  line `( vii ) civil aviation;`
  line `( viii ) shipping and transport;`
  line `( f ) five members to be appointed by the Central Government by rotation in the alphabetical order`
  line `to represent the St ates and the Union territories:`
  line `Provided that an appointment under this clause shall be made on the recommendation of the`
  line `Government of the State, or as the case may be, the Union territory concerned;`
  line `( g ) seven members to be appointed by the Central Govern ment to represent, —`
  line `( i ) the Indian C ouncil of Agricultural Research;`
  line `( ii ) the National Horticulture Board;`
  line `( iii ) the National Agricultural Co - operative Marketing Federation;`
  line `( iv ) the Central Food Technological Research Institute;`
  line `( v ) th e Indian Institute of Packaging;`
  line `( vi ) the Spices Export Promotion Council; and`
  line `( vii ) the Cashew nut Export Promotion Council;`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-5
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Page 5`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  sourcePage 5
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line 5
  line `( h ) twelve members to be appointed by the Central Government to represent, —`
  line `( i ) fruit an d vegetable products industries;`
  line `( ii ) meat, poultr y and dairy products industries;`
  line `1 [( iii ) other Scheduled products or Special products industries;]`
  line `( iv ) packaging industry:`
  line `Provided that the number of members appointed to represent any of the groups of industries`
  line `specified in sub - clauses ( i ) to ( iii ) or the industry specified in sub - clause ( iv ) shall in no case be less`
  line `than two;`
  line `( i ) two members to be appointed by the Central Government from amongst specialists and`
  line `scientists in the field of agriculture, economics and marketing of Scheduled products.`
  line `( 5 ) The t erm of office of the members, other than the member referred to in clause ( b ) of`
  line `sub - section ( 4 ) and the manner of filling vacancies among, and the procedure to be followed in the`
  line `discharge of their functions by, the members shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 6 ) Any officer of the Central Government, not being a member of the Authority, when deputed by`
  line `that Government in this behalf, shall have the right to attend meetings of the Authority and take part in the`
  line `proceedings thereof but shall not be entitled to vote.`
  line `( 7 ) No act or proceeding of the Authority or any committee appointed by it under s ectio n 9 shall be`
  line `invalid merely by reason of —`
  line `( a ) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Authority or such committee; or`
  line `( b ) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a member of the Authority or such`
  line `committee; or`
  line `( c ) any irregularity in the procedure of the Authority or such committee not affecting the merits of`
  line `the case.`
  line `( 8 ) The Authority shall meet at such times and pl aces and shall observe such rules of procedure in`
  line `regard to the transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at its meetings) as may be`
  line `provided by the regulations.`
  line `5. Salary and A llowances and other conditions of service of Chairman and a llowances of`
  line `members. — ( 1 ) The Chairman shall be entitled to such salary and allowances and shall be subject to such`
  line `conditions of service in respect of leave, pension, provident fund and other matters as may, from time to`
  line `time, be fixed by the Central Government.`
  line `( 2 ) The other members of the Authority shall receive such allowances as may be fixed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line `( 3 ) A member, other than the ex officio member, may resign his office by giving notice thereof in`
  line `writing to the Central Government and on such resignation being accepted, he shall be deemed to have`
  line `vacated his office.`
  line `6. Chairman to be chief executive. — The Chairman shall be the chief executive of the Authority and`
  line `shall exercise such powers and perform such duties as may be prescribed.`
  line `7. Secretary of the Authority and other staff. — ( 1 ) The Central Government shall appoint a`
  line `Secretary to the Authority who shall exercise such powers and perform such duties as may be prescribed`
  line `or as may be delegated to him by the Chairman.`
  line `( 2 ) The Secretary shall be entitled to such salary and allowances and shall be subject to such`
  line `conditions of service in respect of leave, pension, provident fund and such other matters as may, from`
  line `time to time, be fixed by the Central Government.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2009, s. 4, for sub - clause ( iii ) (w.e.f. 13 - 10 - 2008 ).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-6
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Page 6`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  sourcePage 6
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `( 3 ) Subject to such control and restrictions as may be prescribed, the Authority may appoint such`
  line `other officers and employees, as may be necessary, for the efficient performance of its functions and the`
  line `method of appointment, the scale of pay and allowances and other conditions of service of such other`
  line `officers and employees of the Authority shall be such as may be provided by the Authority by regulations.`
  line `( 4 ) The Chairman, the Secretary and other officers and employees of the Authority shall not`
  line `undertake any work unconnected with their duties under this Act except with the permission of the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line `8. Special provision for transfer of employees to the Authority. — ( 1 ) On the establishment of the`
  line `Authority, it shall be lawful for the Central Government to transfer to the Authority, by order, and with`
  line `effect from such date or dates as may be specified in the order, any officer or other employee holding`
  line `office as such in the Processed Foods Export Promotion Council (hereafter in this section referred to as`
  line `th e Council) immediately before the date on which the Authority is established:`
  line `Provided that the scale of pay of the post in the Authority to which such officer or oth er employee is`
  line `transferred shall not be lower than the scale of pay of the post he was hol ding immediately before such`
  line `transfer and the other terms and conditions of service (including pension, leave, provident fund and`
  line `medical benefits) of the post to which he is transferred shall not be less favourable than the terms and`
  line `conditions of service in relation to the post held by him immediately before such transfer.`
  line `( 2 ) An order under sub - section ( 1 ) may be made so as to have retrospective effect from a date not`
  line `earlier than the date of the commencement of this Act.`
  line `( 3 ) Before any order is issued u nder sub - section ( 1 ), all officers and employees of the Council shall`
  line `be given an option to express, in such form as may be prescribed, and within such time as may be`
  line `specified in that behalf by the Central Government, their willingness or otherwise to bec ome employees`
  line `of the Authority and such option once exercised shall be final:`
  line `Provided that no order under sub - section ( 1 ) shall be made in relation to any officer or other`
  line `employee s of the Council who has intimated his intention of not becoming an employee of the Authority`
  line `within the time specified in that behalf:`
  line `Provided further that such of the officers and employees of the Council who do not express, within`
  line `the time specified in that behalf, their intention of becoming the employees of the Authority, shall be dealt`
  line `with in the same manner and in accordance with the same laws and standing orders as would have applied`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Act to the employees of the Council in the event of the`
  line `reduction of the strength of the officers and employees of the Council.`
  line `( 4 ) An officer or other employee transferred by an order made under sub - section ( 1 ) shall, on and`
  line `from the date of transfer, cease to be an employee of the Council and become an officer or other`
  line `employee of the Authority with such designation as the Authority may determine and shall, subject to the`
  line `provisions of the proviso to sub - section ( 1 ), be governed by the regulations made by the Authority under`
  line `this Act in respect of remuneration and other conditions of service (including pension, leave, provident`
  line `fund and medical benefits) and shall continue to be an officer or other employee of the Authority unless`
  line `and until his employment is duly terminated by the Authority:`
  line `Provided that till such time as the regulations referred to above governing the conditions of service of`
  line `its officers or other employees are framed by the Authority, the relevant laws and standing orders`
  line `applicable to the officers and emplo yees of the Council shall continue to be applicable to them.`
  line `( 5 ) If a question arises whether the terms and conditions of service prescribed in the regulations`
  line `framed by the Authority in respect of any matter, including remuneration, pension, leave, provid ent fund`
  line `and medical benefits, are less favourable than those attached to the post held by an officer or other`
  line `employee immediately before his transfer to the Authority, the decision of the Central Government in the`
  line `matter shall be final.`
  line `9. Committees of the Authority. — ( 1 ) The Authority may appoint such committees as may be`
  line `necessary for the efficient discharge of its duties and performance of its functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-7
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Page 7`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  sourcePage 7
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line 7
  line `( 2 ) The Authority shall have the po wer to co - opt as members of any committee appointed under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) s uch number of persons, who are not members of the Authority as it may think fit and the`
  line `persons so co - opted shall have the right to attend the meetings of the committee and take part in its`
  line `proceedings but sha ll not have the right to vote.`
  line `( 3 ) The persons co - opted as members of a committee under sub - section ( 2 ) shall be entitled to receive`
  line `such allowances for attending meetings of the committee as may be fixed by the Central Government.`
  line `10. Functions of the Aut hority. — ( 1 ) It shall be the duty of the Authority to undertake, by such`
  line `measures as it thinks fit, the development and promotion, under the control of the Central Government, of`
  line `export of Scheduled products.`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub - section ( 1 ), the measures referred to`
  line `therein may provide for —`
  line `( a ) the development of industries relating to the Scheduled products for export by way of`
  line `providing financial assistance or otherwise for undertaking surveys and feasibility s tudies,`
  line `participation in the equity capital through joint ventures and other reliefs and subsidy schemes;`
  line `( b ) the registration of persons as exporters of the Scheduled products on payment of such fees as`
  line `may be prescribed;`
  line `( c ) the fixing of standards and s pecifications for the Scheduled products for the purposes of`
  line export;
  line `( d ) the carrying out of inspection of meat and meat products in any slaughterhouse, processing`
  line `plant, storage premises, conveyances or other places where such products are kept or handled for the`
  line `purpose of ensuring the quality of such products;`
  line `( e ) the improving of packaging of the Scheduled products;`
  line `( f ) the improving of the marketing of the Scheduled products outside India;`
  line `( g ) the promotion of export oriented production and development of the Scheduled products;`
  line `( h ) th e collection of statistics from the owners of factories or establishments engaged in the`
  line `production, processing, packaging, marketing or export of the Scheduled products or from such other`
  line `persons as may be prescribed on any matter relating to the Scheduled products; and the publication of`
  line `the statistics so collected, or of any por tions thereof or extracts there from;`
  line `( i ) the training in various aspects of the industries connected with the Scheduled products;`
  line `( j ) such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line `1 [ 10A. Functions in respect of Special products, etc. — Without prejudice to any law for the time`
  line `being in force, it shall be the duty of the Authority to undertake, by such measures as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Central Government for registration and protection of the Intellectual Propert y rights in respect of`
  line `Special products in India or outside India.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purpose of this section “ Intellectual Property ” means any right to intangible`
  line `property, namely, trade marks, designs, patents, geographical indications or any other sim ilar intangible`
  line `property, under any law for the time being in force.]`
  line `11. Power to supersede the Authority. — ( 1 ) If the Central Government is of the opinion that the`
  line `Authority is unable to perform, or has persistently made default in the performance of, the duty imposed`
  line `on it by or under this Act or has exceeded or abused its powers, or has wilfully or without sufficient`
  line `cause, failed to comply with any direction issued by the Central Government under s ection 20, the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification i n the Official Gazette, supersede the Authority for such period as may`
  line `b e specified in the notification:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 0 of 2009, s. 5 (w.e.f. 13 - 10 - 2008 ).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-8
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Page 8`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  sourcePage 8
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line 8
  line `Provided that before issuing a notification under this sub - section, the Central Government shall give`
  line `reasonable time to the Authority to show cause wh y it should not be superseded and shall consider the`
  line `explanation and objections, if any, of the Authority.`
  line `( 2 ) Upon the publication of a notificat ion under sub - section ( 1 ) supers eding the Authority, —`
  line `( a ) all the members of the Authority shall, notwithstanding that their term of office has not`
  line `ex pired as from the date of super session, vacate their offices as such members;`
  line `( b ) all the powers and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act, be exercised or`
  line `performed by or on behalf of the Authority sh all, during the period of super session, be exercised and`
  line `performed by such person or persons as the Central Government may direct;`
  line `( c ) all property vested in the Authority shall, during the period of supersession, vest in the Central`
  line `Govern ment.`
  line `( 3 ) On the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ), the Central Government may —`
  line `( a ) extend the period of super session for such further period as it may consider necessary; or`
  line `( b ) r econstitute the Authority in the manner provided in s ection 4.`
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `R EGISTRATION`
  line `12. Registration of exporters. — ( 1 ) Every person exporting any one or more of the Scheduled`
  line `products shall, before the expiration of one month from the date on which he undertakes such export or`
  line `before the expiration of three months from the date of coming into force of this section, whichever is`
  line `later, apply to the Authority to be registered as an exporter of the Scheduled product or Scheduled`
  line `products:`
  line `Provided that the Authority may, for suf ficient reason, extend the time - limit for registration by such`
  line `period as it thinks fit.`
  line `( 2 ) Registration once made shall continue to be in force until it is cancelled by the Authority.`
  line `13. Application, cancellation, fee payable and o ther matters relating to registration. — The form`
  line `of appl ication for registration under s ection 12 and for the cancellation of such registration, the fee`
  line `payable on such applications, the particulars to be included in such applications, the procedure to be`
  line `f ollowed in granting and cancelling registration and the registers to be kept by the Authority shall be such`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line `14. Returns to be made by exporters. — ( 1 ) Every exporter, referred to in sub - section ( 1 ) of`
  line `s ection 12, shall furnish to the Authority at the prescribed time and in the prescribed manner such returns`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 2 ) The Authority may authorise a member or any of its officers to inspect any processing plant or`
  line `any other establishment of the exporter at any time to veri fy the accuracy of any return made under this`
  line section.
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `F INANCE, ACCOUNTS AND AUDIT`
  line `15. Grants or loans by the Central Government. — The Central Government may, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Authority by way of grants or loans`
  line `such sums of money as the Central Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-9
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Page 9`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  sourcePage 9
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line 9
  line `16. Con stitution of Agricultural and Processed Food Products Export Development Fund. — ( 1 )`
  line `There shall be formed a Fund to be called the Agricultural and Processed Food Products Export`
  line `Development Fund and there shall be credited thereto —`
  line `( a ) any sums of money which the Central Government may, after due appropriation made by`
  line `Parliament by law in this behalf, provide from and out of the proceeds of the cess credited under`
  line `s ection 4 of the Agricultural and Processed Food Products Export Cess Ac t, 1985, af ter deducting`
  line `there from the expenses of collection of the cess a nd the amount, if any, refunded;`
  line `( b ) all fees levied and collected in respect of registration and other matters under t his Act or the`
  line `rules made there under;`
  line `( c ) any grants or loans that may be made by the Central Government for the purposes of this Act`
  line `under s ection 15; and`
  line `( d ) any grants or loans that may be made by any State Government, voluntary organisation or`
  line `other institution for the purposes of this Act:`
  line `Provided that no such grant, loan or donation shall be credited to the Fund except with the prior`
  line `approval of the Central Government.`
  line `( 2 ) The Fund shall be applied for —`
  line `( a ) meeting the cost of the measures referred to in s ection 10;`
  line `( b ) meeting the salaries, allowances and other remuneration of the members, officers and other`
  line `employees, as the case may be, of the Authority;`
  line `( c ) meeting the other administrative expenses of the Authority and any other expenses authorised`
  line `by or under this Act; and`
  line `( d ) repayment of any loan.`
  line `17. Borrowing powers of the Authority. — Subject to such rules as may be made in this behalf, the`
  line `Authority shall have power to borrow on the security of the Agricultural and Processed Food Products`
  line `Export Development Fund or any other asset for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line `18. Accounts and audit. — ( 1 ) The Authority shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts, in such form as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Governm ent in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor - General of India.`
  line `( 2 ) The accounts of the Authority shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor - General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connectio n with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Authority to the Comptroller and Auditor - General.`
  line `( 3 ) The Comptroller and Auditor - General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Authority shall have the same r ights and privileges and the authority`
  line `in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor - General generally has in connection with`
  line `the audit of Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of`
  line `books, accoun ts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any of the offices of`
  line `the Authority.`
  line `( 4 ) The accounts of the Authority as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor - General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `C ONTROL BY THE C ENTRAL G OVERNMENT`
  line `19. Power to prohibit or control imports and exports of Scheduled products. — ( 1 ) The Central`
  line `Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make provision for prohibiting, restricting`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-10
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Page 10`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  sourcePage 10
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line 10
  line `or otherwise controlling the import or export of the Scheduled products, either generally or in specified`
  line `classes of cases.`
  line `( 2 ) All Scheduled products to which any order under sub - section ( 1 ) applies, shall be deemed to be`
  line `goods of which the export has been prohibited under s ection 11 of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962),`
  line `and all the provisions o f that Act shall have effect accordingly.`
  line `( 3 ) If any person contravenes any order made under sub - section ( 1 ), he shall, without prejudice to any`
  line `confiscation or penalty to which he may be liable under the provisions of the Customs Act, 1962`
  line `(52 o f 1962), as applied by sub - section ( 2 ), be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
  line `20. Directions by the Central Government. — The Authority shall carry out such directions as may`
  line `be issued to it from time to time by the Central Government for the efficient administration of this Act.`
  line `21. Returns and reports. — ( 1 ) The Authority shall furnish to the Central Government at such time`
  line `and in such form and manner as may be prescribed or as the Central Government may direct, such returns`
  line `and statements and such particulars in regard to any proposed or existing programme for the promotion`
  line `and development of the exp ort of the Scheduled products, as the Central Government may, from time to`
  line `time, require.`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub - section ( 1 ), the Authority shall, as soon as possible,`
  line `after the end of each financial year, submit to the Central Gove rnment a report in such form and before`
  line `such date, as may be prescribed, giving a true and full account of its activities, policy and programmes`
  line `during the previous financial year.`
  line `( 3 ) A copy of the report received under sub - section ( 2 ) shall be laid, as s oon as may be, after it is`
  line `received, before each House of Parliament.`
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `22. Penalty for making false reports. — Any person who, being required by or under this Act to`
  line `furnish any return, fails to furnish such return or furnishes a return containing any particular which is false`
  line `and which he knows to be false or does not believe to be true shall be punishable with fine which ma y`
  line `extend to five hundred rupees.`
  line `23. Penalties for obstructing a member or officer of the Authority in the d ischarge of his duty`
  line `and for failure to produce books and records. — Any person who —`
  line `( a ) obstructs any member authorised by the Chairman in writing or any officer or other employee`
  line `of the Authority authorised in this behalf by the Central Government or by the Authority, in the`
  line `exercise of any power conferred, or in the discharge of any duty impo sed on him by or under this Act;`
  line or
  line `( b ) having control over or custody of any account book or other record fails to p roduce such book`
  line `or record when required to do so by or under this Act,`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line `24. Other penalties. — Whoever contra venes or attempts to contravene or abets the contravention of`
  line `the provisions of this Act or of any rules made hereunder other than the provisions, the punishment for the`
  line `contravention wh ereof has been provided for in s ections 19, 22 and 23, shall be punish able with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand`
  line `rupees, or with both and in the case of a continuing contravention with an additional fine which may`
  line `extend to fifty rupees for every day during which such contravention continues after conviction for the`
  line `first such contravention.`
  line `25. Offences by companies. — ( 1 ) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-11
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Page 11`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  sourcePage 11
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line 11
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company as well as the company shall be d eemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub - section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed w ithout his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 1 ), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offe nce has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guil ty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “ company ” means any body corporate and includes a firm or o ther association of individuals;`
  line and
  line `( b ) “ director ”, in relation to a firm, means a partner in t he firm.`
  line `26. Jurisdiction of court. — No court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Magistrate of`
  line `the first class shall try any offence punishable under this Act.`
  line `27. Previous sanction of the Central Government. — No prosecution for any offence punishable`
  line `under this Act shall be instituted except with previous sanction of the Central Government.`
  line `2 8. Protection of action taken in good faith. — No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie agains t the Central Government, or the Authority or any committee appointed by it, or any member of`
  line `the Authority or such committee, or any officer or other employee of the Central Government or of the`
  line `Authority or any other person authorised by the Central Gove rnment or the Authority, for anything which`
  line `is in good faith done or intended to be done under t his Act or the rules made there under.`
  line `2 9. Power to delegate. — The Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct that any power exerc isable by it under this Act (not being the power to make rules under`
  line `s ection 32) may also be exercised in such cases and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified`
  line `in the order, by such officer or authority as may be specified therein.`
  line `30. Suspension of operation of this Act. — ( 1 ) If the Central Government is satisfied that`
  line `circumstances have arisen rendering it necessary that certain of the restrictions imposed by this Act`
  line `should cease to be imposed or if it considers necessary or expedi ent so to do in the public interest, it may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, suspend or relax to such extent and either indefinitely or for such`
  line `period as may be specified in the notification, the operation of all or any of the provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the operation of any provision of this Act has under sub - section ( 1 ) been suspended or`
  line `relaxed indefinitely, such suspension or relaxation may, at any time while this Act remains in force, be`
  line `removed by the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette.`
  line `31. Application of other laws not barred. — The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to and`
  line `not in derogation of the provisions of any other law for the time being in force.`
  line `32. Power to make rules. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the term of office of the members [ other than the member referred to in clause ( b ) of`
  line `sub - section ( 4 ) of s ection 4 ], the manner of filling vacanci es among, and the procedure to b e followed`
  line `in the discharge of their functions by the members, under sub - section ( 5 ) of s ection 4;`
  line `( b ) the powers which may be exercised and the duties which may be performed by the Chairman`
  line `as the chief executive of the Authority under s ection 6;`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-12
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Page 12`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  sourcePage 12
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line 12
  line `( c ) the powers which may be exercised and the duties which shall be per formed by the Secretary`
  line `of the Authority under sub - section ( 1 ) of s ection 7;`
  line `( d ) the control and restrictions subject to which other officers and employees may be appointed`
  line `by the Authority under sub - section ( 3 ) of s ection 7;`
  line `( e ) the form in which and the time within which option m ay be given by the officers and`
  line `employees of the Processed Foods Export Promotion Council under sub - section ( 3 ) of s ection 8;`
  line `( f ) payment of fees for the registration of exporters of Scheduled products under clause ( b ) of`
  line `sub - section ( 2 ) of s ection 10;`
  line `( g ) persons other than the owners from whom the collection of statistics in respect of any matter`
  line `relating to Scheduled products may be made under clause ( h ) of sub - section ( 2 ) of s ection 10;`
  line `( h ) the additional matters in res pect of which the Authority may undertake measures in the`
  line `discharge of its functions under clause ( j ) of sub - section ( 2 ) of s ection 10;`
  line `1 [( ha ) the measures for registration and protection of the Intellectual Property rights under section`
  line 10A;]
  line `( i ) the form and the manner of making application for registration and for cancellation of`
  line `registration, the fee payable on such ap plication and the procedure to b e followed in granting and`
  line `cancelling registration and the conditions gove rning such registration, under s ection 13;`
  line `( j ) the time at which and the manner in which an exporter shall furnish returns to the Authority`
  line `under sub - section ( 1 ) of s ection 14;`
  line `( k ) the form in which the accounts of the Authority shall be maintained under sub - section ( 1 ) of`
  line `s ection 18;`
  line `( l ) the form and manner in which and the time at which the Authority shall furnish returns and`
  line `statements to the Central Government under sub - section ( 1 ) of s ection 21;`
  line `( m ) the form in which and the date before which the Authority shall furnish to the Central`
  line `Government the report of its activities and programme under sub - section ( 2 ) of s ection 21;`
  line `( n ) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed under this Act.`
  line `33. Power to make regulations. — ( 1 ) The Authority may, with the previous sanction of the Central`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations not inconsistent with the provisions`
  line `of th is Act and the rules made there under, to provide for all matters for which provision is necessary or`
  line `expedient for the purposes of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such regulations`
  line `may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the times and places at which meetings of the Authority or any committee thereof, shall be`
  line `held and the procedure t o be followed thereat and the number of members which shall form a quorum`
  line `at a meeting under sub - secti on ( 8 ) of s ection 4;`
  line `( b ) the method of appointment, the conditions of service and the scales of pay and allowances of`
  line `any of the officers and other employees of the Authority under sub - section ( 3 ) of s ection 7;`
  line `( c ) generally for the efficient conduct of the affairs of the Authority.`
  line `( 3 ) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, modify or rescind any`
  line `regulation sanctioned by it and the regulation so modified or rescinded shall have effect only in suc h`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `rescission shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything done under the regulation before its`
  line `modification or rescission.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 0 of 2009, s. 6 (w.e.f. 13 - 10 - 2008 ).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-13
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Page 13`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  sourcePage 13
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line 13
  line `34. Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament. — Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it`
  line `is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation, as`
  line `the case may be, or b oth Houses agree that the rule or regulation, as the case may be, should not be made,`
  line `the rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be o f no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulmen t shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule or regulation.`
  line `1 [ 3 5. Validation. — All things done, or, omitted to be done, and all actions or measures taken, or, not`
  line `taken, during the period beginning on or after the 13th day of October, 2008 and ending immediately`
  line `before the date of commencement of the Agricultural and Processed Food Products Export Development`
  line `Authority (Amendment) Act, 2009 (20 of 2009), shall, in so far as they are in conformity with the`
  line `provision s of this Act, as amended by the Agricultural and Processed Food Products Export Development`
  line `Authority (Amendment) Act, 2009, be deemed to have been done, or, omitted to be done, or, taken, or,`
  line `not taken, under the provisions of this Act, as amended by the Agricultural and Processed Food Products`
  line `Export Development Authority (Amendment) Act, 2009, as if such provisions were in force at the time`
  line `such things were done or omitted to be done and actions or measures taken or not taken during the said`
  line period.]
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 0 of 2009, s. 7 (w.e.f. 13 - 10 - 2008 ).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
